node.text: This video only shows a fraction of the amazing father you are but I am so lucky to be able to witness it first hand every single day. I feel so content knowing my children are in the very best hands. They’re cared for above and beyond and their confidence will be unwavering thanks to you. You truly are magnificent. This title was made for you. We love you so much.

Cover the bottom of the pot with a layer of any oil of your choosing.

Turn heat to medium.

Place two kernels in the pot and cover with lid. Wait until kernels pot. (This may take a bit but don’t worry!) Once the two kernels pop, remove from heat, turn off stove and wait about 30 seconds! 
Then return to stove top, turn the heat back to medium. Pour about 1/3 cup of kernels into your pot. Should pay flat across the bottom and not cover one another. Place lid on top.

Once they start popping, tilt the lid so the steam is released.

Every so often, shake and shimmy the pot. This allows for the kernels to get cooked evenly. 
Once all popcorn has popped and the popping slows down (there is more than 2 seconds between pops) take them off heat and immediately pour into bowl!

Top with whatever seasons & spices you like!

Xx ❤️

node.text:
I HAVE UNCONDITIONAL LOVE FOR MYSELF!!! 💚💚💚

I don’t always like myself, I annoy the heck out of myself sometimes. I tell myself “you’re not pretty enough, you’re not healed enough, you’re not smart enough, you’re not a good enough mother or wife, you don’t do x,y, and z!” and the list goes on. I can be so mean and unfriendly in my darkest moments. BUT I will always go back and meet myself with the space to feel out those big emotions and be vulnerable. I will love myself through every step of the journey. So say it with me: I LOVE MYSELF UNCONDITIONALLY! 🧡I deserve that kind of love and security from the person who knows me the best; ME! 👩🏻‍🦰
